:[2174,2230]},{"content":"The device entity tracks information about when a POS register is activated, the type of client that is being used, and the application package that has been deployed to a specific device.","pos":[2231,2419]},{"content":"Devices can be of two types: <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Retail modern POS<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> (MPOS) or <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Retail Cloud POS<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> (Cloud POS).","pos":[2420,2514],"source":" Devices can be of two types: **Retail modern POS** (MPOS) or **Retail Cloud POS** (Cloud POS)."},{"pos":[2521,2525],"content":"MPOS","linkify":"MPOS","nodes":[{"content":"MPOS","pos":[0,4]}]},{"content":"MPOS is a POS client application that is installed on Windows 8.1 or a later PC-based operating system.","pos":[2527,2630]},{"content":"If the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Retail modern POS<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> application type is mapped to a device, the download package can be specified for a particular device.","pos":[2631,2762],"source":" If the **Retail modern POS** application type is mapped to a device, the download package can be specified for a particular device."},{"content":"The download package can be customized to include different versions of the installation package.","pos":[2763,2860]},{"content":"The ability to deploy different packages provides flexibility in cases where different POS registers might need different integrations.","pos":[2861,2996]},{"content":"MPOS is deployed together with a built-in hardware station.","pos":[2997,3056]},{"pos":[3063,3072],"content":"Cloud POS","linkify":"Cloud POS","nodes":[{"content":"Cloud POS","pos":[0,9]}]},{"content":"Cloud POS is a browser-based POS.","pos":[3074,3107]},{"content":"Because it runs in the browser, Cloud POS doesn't require Windows 8.1 or a later PC-based operating system.","pos":[3108,3215]},{"content":"If the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Retail Cloud POS<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> application type is mapped to a specific device in the back office, that device can be used through the browser with no need to download or install a package.","pos":[3216,3402],"source":" If the **Retail Cloud POS** application type is mapped to a specific device in the back office, that device can be used through the browser with no need to download or install a package."},{"content":"Cloud POS requires a hardware station to use hardware beyond keyboard wedge based bar code scanning.","pos":[3403,3503]},{"pos":[3509,3525],"content":"Hardware profile","linkify":"Hardware profile","nodes":[{"content":"Hardware profile","pos":[0,16]}]},{"content":"Navigation: Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Commerce<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Channel setup<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>POS setup<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>POS profiles<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p5\">**</bpt>Hardware profiles<ept id=\"p5\">**</ept>.","pos":[3527,3649],"source":"Navigation: Click **Commerce** &gt; **Channel setup** &gt; **POS setup** &gt; **POS profiles** &gt; **Hardware profiles**."},{"content":"A hardware profile identifies the hardware that is connected to a POS register or a hardware station.","pos":[3650,3751]},{"content":"The hardware profile is also used to specify the payment processor parameters that should be used during communication with the payment software development kit (SDK).","pos":[3752,3919]},{"content":"(The payment SDK is deployed as part of the hardware station.)","pos":[3920,3982]},{"pos":[3988,4004],"content":"Hardware station","linkify":"Hardware station","nodes":[{"content":"Hardware station","pos":[0,16]}]},{"content":"Navigation: Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Retail and commerce<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Channels<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Retail stores<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> <ph id=\"p