23],"source":" You can find the POS registers at **Retail and commerce** &gt; **Channel setup** &gt; **POS setup** &gt; **Registers**."},{"content":"After you've assigned the hardware profile, sync changes to the channel database by using the “Registers” distribution schedule.","pos":[5724,5852]},{"content":"You can find the distribution schedules at <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Retail and commerce<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Retail IT<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Distribution schedule<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>.","pos":[5853,5970],"source":" You can find the distribution schedules at **Retail and commerce** &gt; **Retail IT** &gt; **Distribution schedule**."},{"content":"Next, set up a \"local\" hardware station on the channel.","pos":[5971,6026]},{"content":"Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Retail and commerce<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Channels<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Retail stores<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>All retail stores<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept>, and select a store.","pos":[6027,6145],"source":" Click **Retail and commerce** &gt; **Channels** &gt; **Retail stores** &gt; **All retail stores**, and select a store."},{"content":"Then, on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Hardware stations<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> FastTab, click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Add<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> to add a hardware station.","pos":[6146,6230],"source":" Then, on the **Hardware stations** FastTab, click **Add** to add a hardware station."},{"content":"Enter a description, enter <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>localhost<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> as the host name, and then sync the changes to the channel by using the “Channel configuration” distribution schedule.","pos":[6231,6390],"source":" Enter a description, enter **localhost** as the host name, and then sync the changes to the channel by using the “Channel configuration” distribution schedule."},{"content":"You can find the distribution schedules at <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Retail and commerce<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Retail IT<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Distribution schedule<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>.","pos":[6391,6508],"source":" You can find the distribution schedules at **Retail and commerce** &gt; **Retail IT** &gt; **Distribution schedule**."},{"content":"Finally, in MPOS, use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Select hardware station<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> operation to select the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>localhost<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> hardware station.","pos":[6509,6618],"source":" Finally, in MPOS, use the **Select hardware station** operation to select the **localhost** hardware station."},{"content":"Set the hardware station to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Active<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[6619,6658],"source":" Set the hardware station to **Active**."},{"content":"The hardware profile that is used in this scenario should come from the POS register itself.","pos":[6659,6751]},{"content":"A hardware station profile isn't required for this scenario.","pos":[6752,6812]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Some hardware profile changes, such as changes to cash drawers, require that a new shift be opened after the changes have been synced to the channel.","pos":[6813,6972],"source":"**Note:** Some hardware profile changes, such as changes to cash drawers, require that a new shift be opened after the changes have been synced to the channel."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Cloud POS must use the stand-alone hardware station to communicate with retail peripherals.","pos":[6973,7074],"source":"**Note:** Cloud POS must use the stand-alone hardware station to communicate with retail peripherals."},{"pos":[7080,7133],"content":"MPOS or Cloud POS with a stand-alone hardware station","linkify":"MPOS or Cloud POS with a stand-alone hardware station","nodes":[{"content":"MPOS or Cloud POS with a stand-alone hardware station","pos":[0,53]}]},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\[</ph>caption id=\"attachment<ph id=\"ph2\">\\_</ph>340041\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\"<ph id=\"ph3\">\\]</ph><bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ph id=\"ph4\">![</ph>Shared peripherals<ept id=\"p1\">](./media/shared-300x254.png)](./media/shared.png)</ept> Shared peripherals<ph id=\"ph5\">\\[</ph>/caption<ph id=\"ph6\">\\]</ph> In this scenario, a stand-alone hardware station is shared among MPOS and Cloud POS clients.","pos":[7135,7395],"source":"\\[caption id=\"attachment\\_340041\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\"\\][![Shared peripherals](./media/shared-300x254.png)](./media/shared.png) Shared peripherals\\[/caption\\] In this scenario, a stand-alone hardware station is shared among MPOS and Cloud POS clients."},{"content":"This scenario requires that you create a hardware station profile to specify the download package, port, and hardware profile that the hardware station uses.","pos":[7396,7553]},{"content":"You can find the hardware station profile at <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Retail and commerce<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Channel setup<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>POS setup<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>POS profiles<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p5\">**</bpt>Hardware station profiles<ept id=\"p5\">**</ept>.","pos":[7554,7722],"source":" You can find the hardware station profile at **Retail and commerce** &gt; **Channel setup** &gt; **POS setup** &gt; **POS profiles** &gt; **Hardware station profiles**."},{"content":"After you've created the hardware station profile, navigate to the specific retail channel (<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Retail and commerce<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Channels<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Retail stores<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>All retail stores<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept>), and add a new hardware station.","pos":[7723,7940],"source":" After you've created the hardware station profile, navigate to the specific retail channel (**Retail and commerce** &gt; **Channels** &gt; **Retail stores** &gt; **All retail stores**), and add a new hardware station."},{"content":"Map this new hardware station to the hardware station profile that was previously created.","pos":[7941,8031]},{"content":"Next, provide a description that will help the cashier identify the hardware station.","pos":[8032,8117]},{"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Host name<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field, enter the host machine URL in the following format: <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>https://<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>MachineName:Port<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph>/HardwareStation<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[8118,8251],"source":" In the **Host name** field, enter the host machine URL in the following format: **https://&lt;MachineName:Port&gt;/HardwareStation**."},{"content":"(Replace <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>MachineName:Port<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> with the actual machine name of the hardware station and the port that is specified in the hardware station profile.) For a stand-alone hardware station, you should also specify the electronic funds transfer (EFT) terminal ID.","pos":[8252,8516],"source":" (Replace **&lt;MachineName:Port&gt;** with the actual machine name of the hardware station and the port that is specified in the hardware station profile.) For a stand-alone hardware station, you should also specify the electronic funds transfer (EFT) terminal ID."},{"content":"This value identifies the EFT terminal that is connected to the hardware station when the payment connector communicates with the payment provider.","pos":[8517,8664]},{"content":"Next, from the actual hardware station machine, navigate to the channel, and select the hardware station.","pos":[8665,8770]},{"content":"Then click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Download<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and install the hardware station.","pos":[8771,8829],"source":" Then click **Download**, and install the hardware station."},{"content":"Next, from MPOS or Cloud POS, use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Select hardware station<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> operation to select the hardware station that was previously installed.","pos":[8830,8967],"source":" Next, from MPOS or Cloud POS, use the **Select hardware station** operation to select the hardware station that was previously installed."},{"content":"Select <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Pair<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to establish a secure relationship between the POS and the hardware station.","pos":[8968,9060],"source":" Select **Pair** to establish a secure relationship between the POS and the hardware station."},{"content":"This step must be completed once for every combination of a POS and a hardware station.","pos":[9061,9148]},{"content":"After the hardware station is paired, the same operation is used to make the hardware station active while it's used.","pos":[9149,9266]},{"content":"For this scenario, the hardware profile should be assigned to the hardware station profile rather than the register itself.","pos":[9267,9390]},{"content":"If for some reason a hardware station does not have a hardware profile directly assigned, then the hardware profile assigned to the register is used","pos":[9391,9539]},{"pos":[9544,9562],"content":"Client maintenance","linkify":"Client maintenance","nodes":[{"content":"Client maintenance","pos":[0,18]}]},{"pos":[9567,9576],"content":"Registers","linkify":"Registers","nodes":[{"content":"Registers","pos":[0,9]}]},{"content":"POS registers are managed primarily through the registers themselves, and also through the